  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Report of Saul\u2019s Death by the Amalekite"
      title: "The Report of Saul\u2019s Death by the Amalekite"
      number: 1
      content: 'After the death of Saul, David returned from defeating the Amalekites
        and he stayed at Ziklag two days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'On the third day, a man came from the camp from being with Saul,
        with his clothes torn and with dirt on his head. When he came to David, he
        fell to the ground and bowed down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "David said to him, \u201CWhere did you come from?\u201D He said to
        him, \u201CI have escaped from the camp of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then David said to him, \u201CHow did things go? Please tell me.\u201D
        He answered, \u201CWhen the army fled from the battle, and many of the people
        fell; also, Saul and Jonathan his son died.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then David asked the young man who was reporting to him, \u201CHow
        do you know that Saul and his son Jonathan died?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The young man who was reporting to him said, \u201CI merely happened
        to be on Mount Gilboa. Here Saul was leaning on his spear, and look, the
        chariots and the horsemen were getting close to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When he turned around and saw me, he called to me, and I said, \u2018Here
        I am.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he said to me, \u2018Who are you?\u2019 And I said to him, \u2018I
        am an Amalekite.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said to me, \u2018Please stand over me and kill me, for convulsions
        have seized me, even though my life is still in me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So I stood over him and killed him, for I knew that he could not
        live after his falling; I took the crown that was on his head and the bracelet
        which was on his arm; and here, I have brought them to my lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'David grabbed at his clothes and tore them, as did all of the men
        who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then they mourned and wept and fasted over Saul and Jonathan his
        son until the evening, as well as over the people of Yahweh and over the
        house of Israel because they had fallen by the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then David said to the young man who was reporting to him, \u201CWhere
        are you from?\u201D And he said, \u201CI am the son of an alien man. I am
        an Amalekite.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "David said to him, \u201CHow is it that you were not afraid to stretch
        out your hand to destroy Yahweh\u2019s anointed one?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then David called to one of the young men and said to him, \u201CCome
        near; strike him.\u201D So he struck him down and he died. "
      comments: []
    - name: "16: David Laments Jonathan with the \u201CSong of the Bow\u201D"
      title: "David Laments Jonathan with the \u201CSong of the Bow\u201D"
      number: 16
      content: "David said to him, \u201CYour blood is on your head, for your mouth
        has testified against you by saying, \u2018I killed Yahweh\u2019s anointed
        one!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then David sang this funeral song over Saul and over Jonathan his
        son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he ordered \u201CThe Bow\u201D to be taught to the children of
        Judah. Look, it is written on the scroll of Jashar.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThe glory of Israel is on your high places; how the mighty
        have fallen! "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do not tell it in Gath; do not proclaim it in the streets of Ashkelon,
        lest the daughters of the Philistines rejoice, lest the daughters of the
        uncircumcised exult. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'O mountains of Gilboa, let there be no dew or rain upon you or on
        the fields of grain for offerings, for there the small shield of the mighty
        was defiled, the small shield of Saul was not anointed with oil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'From the blood of the slain, from the fat of the mighty, the bow
        of Jonathan did not turn back, and the sword of Saul did not return without
        effect.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Saul and Jonathan were beloved and pleasant in their lives and were
        not separated in their death. They were swifter than eagles, stronger than
        lions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'O daughters of Israel, weep over Saul, the one who clothed you with
        crimson, the one who adorned your clothing with golden ornaments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'How the mighty have fallen in the midst of the battle; Jonathan lies
        slain on your high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I am distressed over you, my brother Jonathan. you were very dear
        to me; your love was more wonderful to me than the love of women. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "How the mighty have fallen and the weapons of warfare perished.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Moves to Hebron'
      title: David Moves to Hebron
      number: 1
      content: "It happened after this that David inquired of Yahweh, saying, \u201CShall
        I go up into one of the cities of Judah?\u201D And Yahweh said to him, \u201CGo
        up.\u201D David asked, \u201CWhere shall I go up?\u201D And he said, \u201CTo
        Hebron.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So David went up there along with his two wives, Ahinoam from Jezreel
        and Abigail the wife of Nabal the Carmelite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: David Anointed King over Judah at Hebron'
      title: David Anointed King over Judah at Hebron
      number: 3
      content: 'Also, David brought up his men who were with him, each with his household,
        and they settled in the towns of Hebron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the men of Judah came, and they anointed David there as king
        over the house of Judah, and they told David, \u201CThe men of Jabesh-Gilead
        buried Saul.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David sent messengers to the men of Jabesh-Gilead and said to
        them, \u201CMay you be blessed by Yahweh because you did this loyal love
        with your lord, with Saul, and you buried him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now may Yahweh show loyal love and faithfulness with you. I will
        also show the good with you that you have done in this matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Ish-Bosheth over Israel'
      title: Ish-Bosheth over Israel
      number: 7
      content: "So then, let your hands be strong and be valiant, for your lord Saul
        is dead, and the house of Judah has anointed me as king over them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Abner the son of Ner, the commander of Saul\u2019s army, had
        taken Ish-Bosheth the son of Saul and brought him over to Mahanaim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He made him king over Gilead, over the Ashurites, over Jezreel, over
        Ephraim, over Benjamin, and over Israel, all of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Ish-Bosheth the son of Saul was forty years old when he became king
        over Israel and he reigned two years; however, the house of Judah followed
        David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: War between Judah and Israel'
      title: War between Judah and Israel
      number: 11
      content: 'The number of days that David was king over Hebron, over the house
        of Judah, was seven years and six months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Abner the son of Ner and the servants of Ish-Bosheth the son of Saul
        went out from Mahanaim to Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Joab the son of Zeruiah and the servants of David went out,
        and they met at the pool of Gibeon. The one group sat on one side of the
        pool, and the other sat on the other side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Abner said to Joab, \u201CLet the young men come up and fight in
        our presence.\u201D And Joab said, \u201CLet them come up.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So they came forward and passed by in number: twelve for Benjamin
        and for Ish-Bosheth the son of Saul, and twelve from the servants of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then each seized his opponent by the head and each thrust his sword
        in the side of his opponent, so they fell together. So they called the name
        of that place Helkath Hazzurim, which is in Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the battle became increasingly fierce on that day, and Abner
        and the men of Israel were defeated before the servants of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The three sons of Zeruiah were there, Joab and Abishai and Asahel.
        Now Asahel was swift with his feet as one of the gazelles which is in the
        open field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Asahel pursued Abner, and he did not turn aside to the right or
        to the left from going after Abner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Abner turned around and said, \u201CAre you this Asahel?\u201D And
        he said, \u201CYes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Abner said to him, \u201CTurn aside to your right or to your left;
        seize for yourself one of the young men, and take his belongings for yourself.\u201D
        But Asahel was not willing to turn aside from him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Abner said to Asahel once again, \u201CFor your own sake, turn
        aside from following me. Why should I strike you down to the ground? How
        could I show my face to Joab your brother?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But he refused to turn away, so Abner struck him in the stomach with
        the butt of the spear, and the spear went out of his back. He fell there
        and he died on the spot. Then all who came to the place where Asahel fell
        and died just stood there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So Joab and Abishai pursued Abner when the sun went down. And they
        came to the hill country of Ammah, which is before Giah on the way to the
        wilderness of Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The descendants of Benjamin rallied after Abner, and they became
        as one fighting group and stood on the top of a certain hill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Abner called to Joab and said, \u201CWill the sword devour forever?
        Do you not know that there will be bitterness in the end? How long will you
        not tell the people to turn away from pursuing their brothers?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Joab said, \u201CAs God lives, for if you had not spoken, the people
        would surely have gone up in the morning, each one of them from following
        after his brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then Joab blew on the trumpet and all the people stopped, and they
        no longer pursued after Israel, and they did not fight with them again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Abner and his men went through the Arabah all that night, and
        they crossed over the Jordan. They went all the forenoon and came to Mahanaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'After Joab returned from pursuing Abner, he gathered all the people;
        nineteen of the servants of David were missing along with Asahel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The servants of David had killed some of the Benjaminites among the
        men of Abner; three hundred and sixty men had died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then they picked up Asahel and buried him in the grave of his father,
        which was at Bethlehem. Joab and his men went all that night arriving in
        Hebron at first light.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The House of David Grows Stronger'
      title: The House of David Grows Stronger
      number: 1
      content: 'The battle was prolonged between the house of Saul and the house
        of David, but David was growing stronger and stronger while the house of
        Saul was becoming weaker and weaker.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And sons were born to David in Hebron; his firstborn was Amnon by
        Ahinoam from Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'His second was Kileab by Abigail the wife of Nabal the Carmelite;
        the third was Absalom the son of Maacah, who was the daughter of Talmai the
        king of Geshur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The fourth was Adonijah the son of Haggith; the fifth was Shephatiah
        the son of Abital. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sixth was Ithream by Eglah the wife of David. These were born
        to David in Hebron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'As the war between the house of Saul and the house of David was continuing,
        Abner was strengthening himself in the house of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Saul had had a concubine, and her name was Rizpah the daughter of
        Aiah. Then Ish-Bosheth said to Abner, \u201CWhy did you have sex with my
        father\u2019s concubine?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Abner became very angry at the words of Ish-Bosheth, and he said,
        \u201CAm I the head of a dog which is for Judah today? Do I not continue
        to show loyal love with the house of Saul your father, to his brothers, and
        to his friends? I have not let you fall into the hands of David, yet you
        have accused me of sin with this woman today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Thus may God punish Abner, if I do not accomplish what Yahweh has
        sworn to David;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "specifically, to transfer the kingdom from the house of Saul and
        to establish the throne of David over Israel and over Judah from Dan to Beersheba!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Abner Pledges Support for David'
      title: Abner Pledges Support for David
      number: 11
      content: 'And Ish-Bosheth was no longer able to answer Abner because he feared
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Abner sent messengers to David where he was, saying, \u201CTo whom
        does the land belong? Make your covenant with me! Look, my hand is with you
        to bring all of Israel over to you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He said, \u201CGood. I will make a covenant with you. I am asking
        only one thing from you: You shall not see my face unless you bring Michal
        the daughter of Saul when you come to see me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then David sent messengers to Ish-Bosheth the son of Saul, saying,
        \u201CGive me my wife Michal whom I betrothed to myself for a hundred foreskins
        of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Ish-Bosheth sent and took her from her husband, from Paltiel the
        son of Laish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But her husband went with her, weeping all along after her as far
        as Bahurim. Then Abner said to him, \u201CGo and return.\u201D So he returned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The word of Abner came to the elders of Israel, saying, \u201CFor
        quite some time you were seeking David as king over you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So then, bring it about, because Yahweh had said to David, \u201CThrough
        the hand of David my servant I am about to save my people Israel from the
        hand of the Philistines and from the hand of all their enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Abner also spoke privately to Benjamin. Abner also went to speak
        to David in Hebron, all that was good in the eyes of Israel and in the eyes
        of all the house of Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Abner came to David in Hebron and with him were twenty men.
        David had prepared a feast for Abner and for the men who were with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Abner said to David, \u201CLet me get up and go and gather all
        of Israel to my lord the king, that they may make a covenant with you so
        you can reign over all which your soul desires.\u201D So David dismissed
        Abner, and he left in peace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And look, the servants of David and Joab came from the raid, and
        they brought much plunder with them. But Abner was not with David at Hebron,
        for he had dismissed him, and he had gone in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Joab Assassinates Abner'
      title: Joab Assassinates Abner
      number: 23
      content: "When Joab and all the army that was with him came, they told Joab,
        \u201CAbner the son of Ner came to the king, and he sent him away, and he
        left in peace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Joab came to the king and said, \u201CWhat have you done? Abner
        came here to you? Why have you dismissed him that he actually went away?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "You know that Abner the son of Ner came to deceive you. He came to
        learn about your going out and coming in and to know all which you are doing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then Joab went out from David, and he sent messengers after Abner,
        and they brought him back from Bor Hasirah, but David did not know it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When Abner returned to Hebron, Joab took him aside to the middle
        of the gate to speak with him in private. Then he struck him in the stomach
        there and he died, for he had shed the blood of Asahel his brother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "When David heard this afterwards, he said: \u201CI and my kingdom
        are innocent before Yahweh forever for the blood of Abner the son of Ner. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "May the blood come down on the head of Joab and all the house of
        his father. May the house of Joab never lack one with a bodily discharge
        or one with leprosy or one who grasps the distaff or one who falls by the
        sword or one who is lacking food.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So Joab and Abishai, his brother, killed Abner because he had killed
        Asahel, their brother, at Gibeon in the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "David said to Joab and to all the people who were with him, \u201CTear
        your clothing and put on sackcloth and mourn before Abner.\u201D Now King
        David was following after the bier. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And they buried Abner at Hebron. And the king lifted up his voice
        and wept at the grave of Abner, and all the people wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The king sang a lament for Abner and said, \u201CShould Abner have
        died the death of a fool? "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Your hands were not tied and your feet were not in contact with bronze
        fetters. You have fallen as one who falls before sons of wickedness.\u201D
        Then all the people wept over him again.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then all the people came to give David food. Still on that day, David
        swore, \u201CMay God punish me if I taste food or anything before the sun
        goes down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'All the people noticed, and it was good in their eyes, as everything
        that the king did was good in the eyes of all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then all the people and all of Israel realized on that day that the
        king had not desired to kill Abner the son of Ner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then the king said to his servants, \u201CDid you not realize that
        a prince and a great man has fallen today in Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "I am weak today even though anointed king, and these men, the sons
        of Zeruiah, are crueler than I am. May Yahweh pay them back for doing wickedness
        according to their own wickedness.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ish-Bosheth is Assassinated'
      title: Ish-Bosheth is Assassinated
      number: 1
      content: 'When the son of Saul heard that Abner had died in Hebron, his courage
        failed and all of Israel was horrified. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Two of the men, commanders of the raiding bands, were for the son
        of Saul. The name of one was Baanah, and the name of the other was Recab,
        the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite from the descendants of Benjamin; also,
        Beeroth was regarded as belonging to Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Beerothites fled to Gittaim, and they are resident aliens there
        until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '(Now Jonathan the son of Saul had a son who was crippled in the feet.
        He was five years old when the message of Saul and Jonathan came from Jezreel,
        and his nurse had picked him up and fled. It happened that as she was hurrying
        away to flee, he fell and became crippled. His name was Mephibosheth.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, Recab and Baanah, set out,
        they came at the heat of the day to the house of Ish-Bosheth while he was
        taking a noontime rest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They came as far as the middle of the house as if takers of wheat,
        and they struck him in the stomach. Then Recab and Baanah his brother escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When they had come into the house, he was lying on his couch in his
        bedchamber, and they attacked him and killed him. Then they beheaded him,
        and they took his head and went on the way of the Arabah all night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They brought the head of Ish-Bosheth to David at Hebron, and they
        said to the king, \u201CHere is the head of Ish-Bosheth, the son of Saul
        your enemy, who sought your life. Yahweh has given to my lord the king vengeance
        this day on Saul and on his offspring.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then David answered Recab and Baanah his brother, the sons of Rimmon
        the Beerothite, and he said to them, \u201CAs Yahweh lives, who redeemed
        my soul from all trouble, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "when the one who told me, \u201CLook, Saul is dead,\u201D thought
        that he was bringing good news, I seized him and killed him at Ziklag, which
        was as my giving the news back to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "How much more when wicked men kill a righteous man in his house,
        on his bed! So then, shall I not seek his lifeblood from your hand, so that
        I may destroy you from the earth?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then David commanded the young men, and they killed them, and they
        cut off their hands and their feet, and they hung them at the pool at Hebron,
        but the head of Ish-Bosheth they took and buried in the grave of Abner at
        Hebron. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Anointed as King over All of Israel'
      title: David Anointed as King over All of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "So all the tribes of Israel came to David at Hebron, and they said,
        \u201CHere we are, we are your flesh and blood.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For some time, when Saul was king over us, you were leading Israel
        in and out. Yahweh had said to you, \u2018You shall be the shepherd of my
        people Israel, and you will be the leader over Israel.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and King David
        made a covenant with them at Hebron in the presence of Yahweh; then they
        anointed David as king over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David was thirty years old when he began to reign; he reigned forty
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Capture and Growth of Jerusalem'
      title: The Capture and Growth of Jerusalem
      number: 5
      content: 'He reigned over Judah at Hebron for seven years and six months; and
        he reigned over all Israel and Judah at Jerusalem for thirty-three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The king and his men went to Jerusalem, to the Jebusites, the inhabitants
        of the land. They said to David, \u201CYou will not come here, for even the
        blind and the lame can turn you back, saying, \u2018David cannot come here.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'David captured the fortress of Zion, the city of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "David had said, \u201COn that day when we attack the Jebusites, one
        must attack the lame and the blind, those who hate the soul of David, by
        means of the water supply.\u201D For thus the blind and the lame would say,
        \u201CHe cannot come into the house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'David occupied the fortress and called it the city of David. And
        David built all around it from the Millo and inward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'David continued growing stronger and stronger, and Yahweh the God
        of hosts was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Hiram, the king of Tyre, sent messengers to David, along with
        cedar trees and craftsmen skilled in wood and in stone masonry, and they
        built a house for David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'David realized that Yahweh had established him as king over Israel
        and that he had exalted his kingdom because of his people Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'David took more concubines and wives from Jerusalem after he came
        from Hebron, and more sons and daughters were born to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'These are the names of the ones born to him in Jerusalem: Shammua
        and Shobab and Nathan and Solomon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ibhar and Elishua and Nepheg and Japhia; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: War with the Philistines'
      title: War with the Philistines
      number: 16
      content: 'Elishama and Eliada and Eliphelet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When the Philistines heard that they had anointed David as king over
        Israel, all the Philistines went up to seek David, but David heard and went
        down to the stronghold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the Philistines had come, and they spread out in the Valley of
        Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And David inquired of Yahweh, saying, \u201CShall I go up to the
        Philistines? Will you give them into my hands?\u201D Yahweh said to David,
        \u201CGo up, for I will certainly give the Philistines into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So David came to Baal Perazim and defeated them there; and David
        said, \u201CYahweh has burst through my enemies before me like the bursting
        of water.\u201D Therefore he called the name of that place Baal Perazim.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They had left their idols there, so David and his men carried them
        away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Once again the Philistines came up and spread out in the Valley of
        Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So David inquired of Yahweh, but he said, \u201CYou shall not go
        up. Rather, go around to their rear and come to them from opposite the balsam
        trees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And it shall be that when you hear the sound of marching in the tops
        of the balsam trees, then pay attention, for then Yahweh has gone out before
        you to strike down the army of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So David did thus, just as Yahweh had commanded him, and he struck
        down the Philistines from Geba all the way to Gezer. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Brings the Ark of Yahweh to Jerusalem'
      title: David Brings the Ark of Yahweh to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'David again gathered all the chosen men in Israel, thirty thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'David got up and went and all the people who were with him, from
        Baale-judah to bring up from there the ark of God which is called the name,
        the name of Yahweh of hosts, upon which the cherubim sit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They loaded the ark of God on a new utility cart, and they carried
        it from the house of Abinadab, which was on the hill. Now Uzza and Ahio,
        the sons of Abinadab, were driving the new utility cart along. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So they brought it out from the house of Abinadab, which was on the
        hill with the ark of God, and Ahio was going before the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now David and all the house of Israel were dancing before Yahweh,
        with all kinds of musical instruments made from ash trees, and with zithers,
        harps, tambourines, sistrums, and cymbals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When they came to the threshing floor of Nakon, Uzza reached out
        to the ark of God and took hold of it, because the oxen had stumbled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the anger of Yahweh was kindled against Uzza, and God struck
        him down there because of the indiscretion, and he died there beside the
        ark of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'David was angry because Yahweh had burst out against Uzza, and he
        called that place Perez-Uzza until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But David feared Yahweh on that day and said, \u201CHow can the ark
        of Yahweh come to me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'However, David was not willing to bring the ark of Yahweh to himself,
        to the city of David, so David caused it to turn to the house of Obed-Edom
        the Gittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So the ark of Yahweh remained in the house of Obed-Edom the Gittite
        for three months, and Yahweh blessed Obed-Edom and all his household. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It was told to King David, \u201CYahweh has blessed the household
        of Obed-Edom and all that is his because of the ark of God.\u201D So David
        went and brought up the ark of God from the house of Obed-Edom to the city
        of David with jubilation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'It happened that when the carriers of the ark of Yahweh had marched
        six steps that he sacrificed an ox and a fatling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now David was dancing with all his might before Yahweh, and David
        was wearing a linen ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So David and all the house of Israel were bringing up the ark of
        Yahweh with shouts of joyful acclaim and with the sound of the trumpet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It happened that when the ark of Yahweh came into the city of David,
        Michal the daughter of Saul looked down through the window and saw King David
        leaping and dancing before Yahweh, and she despised him in her heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They brought the ark of Yahweh and set it in its place in the middle
        of the tent which David had pitched for it. Then David offered up burnt offerings
        and fellowship offerings in the presence of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When David had finished from the sacrificing of the burnt offerings
        and the fellowship offerings, he blessed the people in the name of Yahweh
        of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then he distributed to all the people, to all the multitude of Israel,
        from man to woman, to each: one ring-shaped piece of bread, one cake of dates,
        and one cake of raisins; and all the people went each to his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When David returned to bless his household, Michal the daughter of
        Saul came out to meet David. She said, \u201CHow the king of Israel honored
        himself today by uncovering himself before the eyes of the maids of his servants,
        as the total exposure of a worthless one.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So David said to Michal, \u201CIn the presence of Yahweh who chose
        me over your father and over his household, to appoint me as leader over
        the people of Yahweh, over Israel, I have celebrated before Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I will demean myself again more than this, and I will be abased in
        my eyes, but with the maids whom you mentioned, with them I will be honored.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So for Michal the daughter of Saul, she had no child until the day
        of her death. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Yahweh Makes a Covenant with David'
      title: Yahweh Makes a Covenant with David
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened that the king settled in his house. (Now Yahweh had given
        rest to him from all his enemies all around.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the king said to Nathan the prophet, \u201CLook, please, I am
        living in a house of cedar, but the ark of God is staying in the middle of
        the tent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Nathan said to the king, \u201CGo and do all that is in your heart,
        for Yahweh is with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But it happened that night, the word of Yahweh came to Nathan, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGo and tell my servant David, \u2018Thus says Yahweh: \u201CAre
        you the one to build for me a house for my dwelling? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I have not dwelt in a house from the day I brought up the Israelites
        from Egypt until this day; rather, I was going about in a tent and in a tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "In all of my going about among all the Israelites, did I speak a
        word with one of the tribes of Israel whom I commanded to shepherd my people
        Israel, saying, \u2018Why did you not build me a cedar house?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So then, thus you shall say to my servant David, \u2018Thus says
        Yahweh of hosts, \u201CI took you from the pasture from following the sheep
        to be a leader over my people, over Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and I have been with you everywhere you went. I have cut off all
        of your enemies from in front of you, and I will make a great name for you,
        as the name of the great ones who are on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will make a place for my people Israel, and I will plant them so
        that they can dwell in their own place. They will not tremble any longer,
        and the children of wickedness will not afflict them again, as in the former
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'In the manner that I appointed judges over my people Israel, I will
        give you rest from all your enemies. And Yahweh declares to you that Yahweh
        will build a house for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When your days are full and you lie down with your ancestors, I will
        raise up your offspring after you who will go out from your body, and I will
        establish his kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He will build a house for my name, and I will establish the throne
        of his kingdom forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will be a father to him, and he will be a son for me, whom I will
        punish when he does wrong, with a rod of men and with blows of the human
        beings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But my loyal love shall not depart from him as I took it from Saul,
        whom I removed from before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: "16: David Responds to Yahweh\u2019s Covenant"
      title: "David Responds to Yahweh\u2019s Covenant"
      number: 16
      content: "Your house and your kingdom shall endure forever before you; your
        throne shall be established forever.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'According to all these words and according to all this vision, this
        Nathan spoke to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then King David went and sat before Yahweh and said, \u201CWho am
        I, my lord Yahweh, and what is my house that you have brought me up to this
        place?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Still, this was insignificant in your eyes, my lord Yahweh, and also
        you have spoken about the house of your servant from afar, and this may be
        the teaching of humans, my lord Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'What more can David say to you? You know your servant, my lord Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Because of your word and according to your heart, you have done all
        of this great thing, in order to let your servant know. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Therefore you are great, my lord Yahweh, for there is no one like
        you, and there is no god except you, in all that we have heard with our ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Who is like your people, like Israel? Israel is the one nation on
        earth whose God led them, in order to redeem a people for himself, and to
        make a name for himself, and to do for you the great and awesome things for
        your land in the presence of your people whom he redeemed for himself from
        Egypt, from the nations and their gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You have established your people Israel for yourself as a people
        forever, and you, O Yahweh, have become their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So then, Yahweh God, the word that you have spoken concerning your
        servant and concerning his house, confirm it forever, and do just as you
        have promised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Your name shall be great forever, and they will say, \u2018Yahweh
        of hosts is God over Israel\u2019; and the house of your servant David shall
        be established before you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For you, O Yahweh of hosts, are God of Israel! You have revealed
        to the ear of your servant, \u2018I will build a house for you\u2019; therefore
        your servant has found courage to pray this prayer to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now, my Lord Yahweh, you alone are God, and your words are true.
        You have promised this good to your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So then, be content and bless the house of your servant to be forever
        in your presence, for you, my Lord Yahweh, have spoken, and because of your
        blessing, may the house of your servant be blessed forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Military Victories Continue"
      title: "David\u2019s Military Victories Continue"
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened afterwards that David attacked the Philistines and subdued
        them, and he took Metheg Ammah from the hands of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When he defeated Moab, he measured them with the cord, making them
        lie on the ground. He measured two cords to kill and the third cord to let
        live. So Moab became servants of David, bringing tribute. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then David struck down Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of Zobah,
        when he went to restore his monument at the Euphrates River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David captured from him one thousand and seven hundred horsemen and
        twenty thousand foot soldiers. David hamstrung all the chariot horses, but
        from them he spared a hundred chariot horses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Aram of Damascus came to help Hadadezer, the king of Zobah,
        David killed twenty-two thousand men of Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'David placed garrisons in Aram of Damascus, so Aram became servants
        of David, bringing tribute. Yahweh protected David everywhere he went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'David took the small round gold shields which had belonged to the
        servants of Hadadezer, and he brought them to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'From Betah and from Berothai, the towns of Hadadezer, King David
        took very many bronze items. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Toi, the king of Hamath, heard that David had defeated all the
        army of Hadadezer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Toi sent Joram his son to King David to greet him and to congratulate
        him because he had fought against Hadadezer and defeated him; for Hadadezer
        had often been at war with Toi. He brought with him objects of silver and
        objects of gold and objects of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'King David dedicated them also to Yahweh along with the silver and
        the gold that he had dedicated from all of the nations which he had subdued; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'from Aram and from Moab and from the Ammonites and from the Philistines
        and from Amalek and from the plunder of Hadadezer the son of Rehob, the king
        of Zobah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So David made a name for himself when he returned from defeating
        Aram in the Valley of Salt, eighteen thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He put garrisons in Edom; all over Edom he put garrisons, and all
        of Edom became servants of David. Yahweh protected David wherever he went. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'David reigned over all of Israel, and he was administering justice
        and righteousness for all his people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the army, and Jehoshaphat the son
        of Ahilud was secretary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Zadok the son of Ahitub and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar were priests
        and Seraiah was scribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Kerethites and the Pelethites,
        and the sons of David were priests. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Cares for Mephibosheth'
      title: David Cares for Mephibosheth
      number: 1
      content: "Then David said, \u201CIs there still anyone who is left for the
        house of Saul that I may show loyal love to him for the sake of Jonathan?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now Saul\u2019s household had a servant whose name was Ziba, so they
        summoned him to David, and the king asked him, \u201CAre you Ziba?\u201D
        He said, \u201CAt your service!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CBut is there still anyone of Saul\u2019s
        household that I may show the loyal love of God with him?\u201D And Ziba
        said to the king, \u201CThere is still a son of Jonathan who is lame in the
        feet.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The king said to him, \u201CWhere is he?\u201D And Ziba said to the
        king, \u201CHe is here in the house of Makir the son of Ammiel in Lo Debar.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So King David sent and brought him from the house of Makir the son
        of Ammiel from Lo Debar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Mephibosheth the son of Jonathan, the son of Saul, came to David.
        And he fell on his face and did obeisance. David said, \u201CMephibosheth,\u201D
        and he said, \u201CI am ready to serve you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then David said to him, \u201CDon\u2019t be afraid, for I will certainly
        show loyal love to you for the sake of Jonathan your father, and I will restore
        to you all the lands of Saul your father. And you shall always eat food at
        my table.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he did obeisance and said, \u201CWhat is your servant that you
        have paid attention to the dead dog like me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "David summoned Ziba the servant of Saul and said to him, \u201CAll
        that was Saul\u2019s and all his household I have given to the son of your
        master. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You shall till the land for him, you and your sons and your servants;
        you shall bring in the produce and it shall be food for the son of your master
        that he may eat. But Mephibosheth the son of your master may always eat food
        at my table.\u201D (Now Ziba had fifteen sons and twenty slaves.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Ziba said to the king, \u201CAccording to all that my master the
        king commands his servant, so your servant will do.\u201D So Mephibosheth
        was eating at his table as one of the sons of the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now Mephibosheth had a young son whose name was Micah, and all of
        the dwelling of the household of Ziba became servants for Mephibosheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Mephibosheth was living in Jerusalem, because he was continually
        eating at the table of the king, even though he was lame in both of his feet. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Ammonites Refuse David\u2019s Loyal Love"
      title: "The Ammonites Refuse David\u2019s Loyal Love"
      number: 1
      content: 'Afterwards the king of the Ammonites died, and his son Hanun ruled
        in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David said, \u201CI will show loyal love with Hanun, the son of Nahash,
        as his father showed loyal love with me.\u201D So David sent to console him
        concerning his father, by the hand of his servants. And the servants of David
        came to the land of the Ammonites.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the commanders of the Ammonites said to Hanun their master, \u201CIn
        your opinion, is David honoring your father because he has sent condolences
        to you? Is it not in order to search the city, to spy it out, and to overthrow
        it that David sent his servants to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Hanun took the servants of David, and he shaved off half of
        their beards and cut their garments off in the middle up to their buttocks,
        then sent them away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Israel Fights Ammon and Aram'
      title: Israel Fights Ammon and Aram
      number: 5
      content: "When they told David, he sent to meet them, for the men were greatly
        ashamed. And the king said, \u201CRemain in Jericho until your beards have
        grown, and then you can return.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the Ammonites saw that they had become odious to David, the
        Ammonites sent word and hired Aram Beth-Rehob and Aram-Zobah, twenty thousand
        infantry; and they also hired the king of Maacah, a thousand men, and the
        men of Tob, twelve thousand men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When David heard, he sent Joab and all the army of mighty warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Ammonites came out and drew up a battle formation at the entrance
        of the gate, but Aram-Zobah and Rehob and the men of Tob and Maacah were
        alone in the open field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Joab saw that the battle was to be fought on two fronts, he
        chose from all the members of the elite troops of Israel and lined them up
        for battle to meet Aram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The rest of the army he placed into the hand of his brother Abishai,
        who arranged them in battle lines to meet the Ammonites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then he said, \u201CIf Aram is stronger than I am, you must become
        my deliverer; but if the Ammonites are too strong for you, then I will come
        to rescue you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Be strong, and let us strengthen ourselves for the sake of the people
        and for the sake of the cities of our God. May Yahweh do what is good in
        his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Joab and all the people who were with him moved forward into the
        battle against Aram, and they fled from before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Arameans Regroup for Attack'
      title: The Arameans Regroup for Attack
      number: 14
      content: 'When the Ammonites saw that Aram had fled, they fled from before
        Abishai and entered the city. Then Joab returned from fighting against the
        Ammonites and came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When the Arameans saw that they were defeated before Israel, they
        gathered themselves together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Hadadezer sent and brought out the Arameans who were beyond
        the Euphrates, and they came to Helam. Now Shobach, the commander of the
        army of Hadadezer, was at their head.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'David was told, so he gathered all Israel and crossed over the Jordan
        and came to Helam. Aram arranged themselves in battle lines to meet David,
        and they fought with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Aram fled before Israel, and David killed from the Arameans seven
        hundred chariot teams and forty thousand horsemen. He struck down Shobach,
        the commander of his army, and he died there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When all the kings, the servants of Hadadezer, saw that he had been
        defeated before Israel, they made peace with Israel and served them, and
        Aram was afraid to help the Ammonites any longer. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Commits Adultery with Bathsheba'
      title: David Commits Adultery with Bathsheba
      number: 1
      content: 'It came about in the spring, at the time kings go out, David sent
        Joab and his servants with him and all of Israel. They ravaged all of the
        Ammonites and besieged Rabbah, but David was remaining in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "It happened late one afternoon that David got up from his bed and
        walked about on the roof of the king\u2019s house, and he saw a woman bathing
        on her roof. Now the woman was very beautiful.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "David sent and inquired about the woman, and someone said, \u201CIs
        this not Bathsheba the daughter of Eliam, the wife of Uriah the Hittite?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then David sent messengers and took her, and she came to him, and
        he slept with her. (Now she had been purifying herself from her uncleanness.)
        And she returned to her house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The woman became pregnant, and she sent and told David, and she said,
        \u201CI am pregnant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So David sent to Joab, \u201CSend Uriah the Hittite to me.\u201D
        So Joab sent Uriah to David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Uriah came to him, and David asked how Joab and the army fared and
        how the war was going.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "David said to Uriah, \u201CGo down to your house, and wash your feet.\u201D
        So Uriah went out from the king\u2019s house, and a gift from the king went
        out after him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Uriah slept at the entrance of the king\u2019s house with all
        the servants of his master and did not go down to his house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They told David, \u201CUriah did not go down to his house.\u201D
        David said to Uriah, \u201CAre you not coming from a journey? Why did you
        not go down to your house?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Uriah said to David, \u201CThe ark and Israel and Judah are living
        in the booths; and my lord Joab and the servants of my lord are camping on
        the surface of the open field; and I, shall I go to my house to eat and to
        drink and to sleep with my wife? By your life and the life of your soul,
        I surely will not do this thing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "David said to Uriah, \u201CRemain here today, and tomorrow I will
        send you away.\u201D So Uriah remained in Jerusalem on that day and the next. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'David invited him, and he ate and drank in his presence so that he
        became drunk, and he went out in the evening to lie on his bed with the servants
        of his lord, but he did not go down to his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And it happened in the morning, David wrote a letter to Joab, and
        he sent it by the hand of Uriah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He had written in the letter, \u201CPut Uriah in the front, in the
        face of the fiercest fighting, then draw back from behind him so that he
        may be struck down and die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When Joab was besieging the city, he put Uriah toward the place which
        he knew there were valiant warriors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The men of the city came out and fought with Joab. Some from the
        army from the servants of David fell; Uriah the Hittite also died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Joab sent and told David all of the news of the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He instructed the messenger, saying, \u201CAs you are finishing to
        speak all the news of the battle to the king, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "if the anger of the king rises and he says to you, \u2018Why did
        you go near the city to fight? Did you not know that they would shoot from
        atop the wall? "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Who killed Abimelech the son of Jerub-bosheth, if not a woman who
        threw an upper millstone on him from atop the wall and he died at Thebez?
        Why did you go near the wall?\u2019 Then you shall say, \u2018Your servant
        Uriah the Hittite also died.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the messenger left, and he came and told David all that Joab
        had sent him to say. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The messenger said to David, \u201CBecause the men overpowered us,
        the men came out to us in the field, but we forced them back to the entrance
        of the gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The archers shot at your servant from atop the wall, and some of
        the servants of the king died; your servant Uriah the Hittite also died.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then David said to the messenger, \u201CThus you shall say to Joab,
        \u2018Do not feel badly about this matter; now one and then another the sword
        will devour. Intensify your attack on the city and overthrow it.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D
        And he encouraged him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When the wife of Uriah heard that Uriah her husband was dead, she
        mourned over her husband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When the mourning was over, David sent and brought her to his household,
        and she became his wife and bore him a son. But the thing which David had
        done was evil in the eyes of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nathan Reproves David'
      title: Nathan Reproves David
      number: 1
      content: "So Yahweh sent Nathan to David, and he came to him and said, \u201CTwo
        men were in a certain city; one was rich and the other was poor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The rich man had very many flocks and herds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'but the poor man had nothing except for one small ewe lamb which
        he had bought. He had nurtured her, and she grew up with him and with his
        children together. She used to eat from his morsel and drink from his cup,
        and she used to lie in his lap and became like a daughter for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And a visitor came to the rich man, but he was reluctant to take
        from his flocks or from his herds to prepare a meal for the traveler when
        he came to him. So he took the ewe lamb of the poor man and prepared it for
        the man who had come to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the anger of David was kindled against the man, and he said
        to Nathan, \u201CAs Yahweh lives, the man who has done this deserves to die!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He shall restore the ewe lamb fourfold because he has done this thing,
        and because he had no pity.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Nathan said to him, \u201CYou are the man! Thus says Yahweh
        the God of Israel: \u2018I anointed you as king over Israel, and I delivered
        you from the hand of Saul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I gave you the household of your master and the women of your master
        into your lap. I also gave you the house of Israel and Judah; if that had
        been too little, I would have added to you much more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Why have you despised the word of Yahweh by doing evil in his eyes?
        Uriah the Hittite you have struck down with the sword, and his wife you have
        taken to yourself as wife! You have killed him with the sword of the Ammonites!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So then, a sword will not turn away from your house forever, because
        you have despised me and have taken the wife of Uriah the Hittite to be your
        wife!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, \u2018Look, I am going to raise up evil against
        you from within your house, and I will take your women before your eyes,
        and I will give them to your neighbor, and he shall sleep with your wives
        in broad daylight.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: David Repents, But the Child Dies'
      title: David Repents, But the Child Dies
      number: 12
      content: "Though you did this in secret, I will do this thing before all of
        Israel in broad daylight!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then David said to Nathan, \u201CI have sinned against Yahweh!\u201D
        Nathan said to David, \u201CYahweh has also forgiven your sin; you shall
        not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But because you have utterly scorned Yahweh in this matter, the son
        born for you will certainly die.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Nathan went to his house, and Yahweh struck the child that the
        wife of Uriah bore for David, and he became ill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'David pleaded with God on behalf of the boy and David fasted. He
        went to spend the night and lay upon the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The elders of his household stood over him to lift him up from the
        ground, but he was not willing, and he did not eat any food with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "It happened on the seventh day that the child died, and the servants
        of David were afraid to tell him that the child was dead, for they said,
        \u201CLook, when the child was alive, we spoke to him, but he would not listen
        to our voice. How can we tell him, \u2018The child is dead\u2019? He may
        do something evil.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When David saw that his servants were whispering together, he realized
        that the child was dead. Then David said to his servants, \u201CIs the child
        dead?\u201D And they said, \u201CHe is dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'David stood up from the ground and washed and anointed himself and
        changed his clothing. Then he went to the house of Yahweh and worshiped,
        and he went to his own house. He asked, so they served him food, and he ate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then his servants said to him, \u201CWhat is this thing that you
        have done? While the child was alive, you fasted and wept; now that the child
        has died, you get up and eat food!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He said, \u201CWhen the child was still alive, I fasted and I wept
        because I thought, \u2018Who knows? Yahweh may have mercy on me that the
        child will live.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But now he is dead. Why should I be fasting? Am I able to return
        him again? I am going to him, but he cannot return to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'David consoled Bathsheba his wife, and he went to her and slept with
        her. She bore a son, and he called him Solomon, and Yahweh loved him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Battle with the Ammonites'
      title: Battle with the Ammonites
      number: 25
      content: 'He sent word by the hand of Nathan the prophet, so he called him
        Jedidiah because of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Joab fought against Rabbah of the Ammonites, and he captured
        the royal city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then Joab sent messengers to David and said, \u201CWe have fought
        against Rabbah, and we captured the city of the waters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So then, gather the remainder of the army and encamp against the
        city and capture it, lest I capture the city and my name be proclaimed over
        it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So David gathered all of the army, and he went to Rabbah and fought
        against it and captured it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "He took the crown of their king from his head. (Now its weight was
        a talent of gold, and there was a precious stone in it and it was put on
        David\u2019s head.) He brought out the plunder of the city in great abundance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'He also brought out the people who were in it and put them to the
        saws and to the iron picks and to the iron axes, and he sent them to the
        place of the brickmakers. Thus he used to do to all the cities of the Ammonites,
        and he and all of the army returned to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amnon Assaults His Sister Tamar'
      title: Amnon Assaults His Sister Tamar
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened afterwards that Absalom the son of David had a beautiful
        sister whose name was Tamar, and Amnon the son of David fell in love with
        her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Amnon was so frustrated that he felt ill because of Tamar his
        sister, because she was a virgin, and it was too difficult in Amnon\u2019s
        eyes to do anything with her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Amnon had a friend whose name was Jonadab the son of Shimeah,
        the brother of David. (Now Jonadab was a very crafty man.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CWhy are you so sullen every morning, O
        son of the king? Will you not tell me?\u201D And Amnon said to him, \u201CI
        am in love with Tamar, the sister of my brother Absalom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Jonadab said to him, \u201CLie down on your bed and appear ill.
        If your father comes to see you, you shall say to him, \u2018Please let Tamar
        my sister come and give me food to eat, and let her prepare the food before
        my eyes, in order that I may see it and eat from her hand.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Amnon lay down and pretended to be ill, and the king came to see
        him. Amnon said to the king, \u201CPlease let Tamar my sister come, and let
        her bake two cakes before my eyes that I may eat from her hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So David sent to the house for Tamar, saying, \u201CPlease go to
        the house of Amnon your brother and prepare food for him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Tamar went to the house of Amnon her brother. Now he was lying down,
        and she took the dough and kneaded it and made cakes before his eyes, and
        she baked the cakes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then she took the pan and poured it out before him, but he refused
        to eat. Then Amnon said, \u201CLet all the men go out from me.\u201D So all
        the men went out from him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Amnon said to Tamar, \u201CBring the food to the private room
        that I may eat from your hand.\u201D So Tamar took the cakes which she had
        made and brought them to Amnon her brother in the private room. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When she brought them near to him to eat, he took hold of her and
        said to her, \u201CCome, lie with me, my sister!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Tamar said to him, \u201CNo, my brother! Do not force me, for
        such a thing has not been done in Israel. Do not do this disgraceful thing! "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As for me, where should I take my disgrace? You will be as one of
        the fools in Israel. So please, speak to the king, for he will not withhold
        me from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But he was not willing to listen to her voice. He was stronger than
        she, and he forced her and lay with her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Amnon hated her very deeply, for the hatred with which he hated
        her was greater than the love with which he had loved her. So Amnon said
        to her, \u201CGet up and go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "She said to him, \u201CNo, because this evil in sending me away is
        greater than the other you have done to me.\u201D But he was not willing
        to listen to her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he called his young man who was serving him and said, \u201CPlease
        send this woman from me to the outside, and bolt the door behind her!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now there was a long-sleeved robe on her, for so they clothed the
        daughters of the king who were virgins, in robes. His servant put her outside,
        and he bolted the door behind her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Tamar put ashes on her head, and she tore the long-sleeved robe which
        was on her. She put her hand on her head, and she went away, crying out as
        she went.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Absalom Kills Amnon'
      title: Absalom Kills Amnon
      number: 20
      content: "Absalom her brother said to her, \u201CWas Amnon your brother with
        you? But now, my sister, be quiet; he is your brother. Do not take this matter
        to heart.\u201D So Tamar remained a desolate woman in the house of Absalom
        her brother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now King David heard all these things, and he became very angry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Absalom did not speak with Amnon either bad or good, for Absalom
        hated Amnon over the matter when he raped Tamar his sister. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "About two full years later, Absalom\u2019s shearers were in Baal
        Hazor, which is near Ephraim, and Absalom summoned all the sons of the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Absalom went to the king and said, \u201CLook, here are your
        servant\u2019s shearers; please let the king and his servants go with your
        servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The king said to Absalom, \u201CNo my son, not all of us shall go,
        so that we not be a burden to you.\u201D And he urged him, but he was not
        willing to go, but he blessed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So Absalom said, \u201CBut will you not let Amnon my brother go with
        us?\u201D And the king said to him, \u201CWhy should he go with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But Absalom pressed him, so he sent Amnon with him and all of the
        sons of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Absalom commanded his servants, saying, \u201CPlease watch. At the
        moment the heart of Amnon is tipsy with wine, then I shall say to you, \u2018Strike
        Amnon down,\u2019 and you shall kill him! Don\u2019t be afraid. Is it not
        I myself who has commanded you? Be courageous and be valiant!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So Absalom\u2019s servants did to Amnon just as Absalom commanded,
        and all the sons of the king got up, and each mounted his mule and fled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "While they were on the way, the message came to David, \u201CAbsalom
        has killed all the sons of the king, and not one of them was left.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then the king rose and tore his garments, and he lay on the ground,
        and all his servants standing by were tearing their garments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Jonadab the son of Shimeah, the brother of David, responded
        and said, \u201CMy lord should not think that all the young men, the sons
        of the king, are dead, because only Amnon is dead. Absalom was talking about
        it, as it was being determined from the day he raped Tamar his sister. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Absalom Flees'
      title: Absalom Flees
      number: 33
      content: "So then, let not my lord the king set his heart on this matter, thinking,
        \u2018All the sons of the king are dead,\u2019 for only Amnon alone is dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So Absalom fled, and the young man who was keeping watch lifted up
        his eyes and saw, and there were many people coming from the road behind
        him from the side of the mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jonadab said to the king, \u201CLook, the sons of the king have come.
        According to the word of your servant, so it has come about.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'When he finished speaking, look, the sons of the king came and they
        lifted up their voice and wept. Also, the king and all his servants wept
        a very great weeping. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Absalom fled and went to Talmai the son of Ammihur, the king of Geshur.
        David mourned over his son day after day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'But Absalom had fled and went to Geshur, and he was there three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'King David longed to go out to Absalom, for he was consoled that
        Amnon had died. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joab Plots to Reconcile David with Absalom'
      title: Joab Plots to Reconcile David with Absalom
      number: 1
      content: 'Joab the son of Zeruiah realized that the mind of the king was on
        Absalom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Joab sent to Tekoa and took from there a wise woman, and he said
        to her, \u201CPlease pretend to mourn and put on garments of mourning. You
        should not anoint yourself with oil, and you must act like this woman who
        has been mourning over the dead for a long time.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then you must go to the king and speak to him according to this word.\u201D
        Thus Joab put the words in her mouth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So the Tekoite woman spoke to the king, and she fell on her face
        to the ground and did obeisance. She said, \u201CHelp me, O king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the king asked her, \u201CWhat do you want?\u201D And she said,
        \u201CTruly I am a widow, and my husband is dead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Your servant had two sons, and they both fought in the open field,
        and there was no one to part them. One struck the other and killed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And look, all of the family has risen up against your servant, and
        they said, \u2018Give up the one who struck his brother, that we may kill
        him in exchange for the life of his brother whom he murdered. We will also
        wipe out the heir,\u2019 and so they would put out my embers which remain,
        by not preserving for my husband a name and a remnant on the face of the
        earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the king said to the woman, \u201CGo to your house, and I myself
        will give the command concerning you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The Tekoite woman said to the king, \u201COn me, my lord the king,
        is the guilt, and on the house of my father, but the king on his throne is
        innocent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The king said, \u201CWhoever has spoken to you, bring him to me,
        and he will not touch you again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then she said, \u201CPlease may the king remember Yahweh your God,
        to prevent the increase of blood avengers who kill, so that they not wipe
        out my son.\u201D He said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives, surely not one hair shall
        fall from your son to the ground.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The woman said, \u201CPlease let your servant speak a word to my
        lord the king.\u201D And he said, \u201CSpeak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The woman said, \u201CBut why have you plotted like this against
        the people of God? By speaking this word, he is guilty not to bring back
        his banished one. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For we must certainly die, and we are as the waters spilled to the
        ground which cannot be gathered. God will not take a life but devises plans
        for a banished person not to be cast out from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now I have come to speak this word to my lord the king, because the
        people made me afraid, and your servant thought, \u2018I will speak to the
        king, perhaps the king will grant the request of his servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For the king will listen, to deliver his servant from the hand of
        the man who seeks to destroy me and my son together from the inheritance
        of God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Your servant also thought, \u2018May the word of my lord the king
        bring rest, for as an angel of God, so is my lord the king, to sense what
        is good and what is bad.\u2019 May Yahweh your God be with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The king answered and said to the woman, \u201CPlease do not withhold
        from me a thing which I am about to ask you.\u201D The woman said, \u201CPlease
        let my lord the king speak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The king asked, \u201CWas the hand of Joab with you in all of this?\u201D
        The woman answered and said, \u201CAs your soul lives, my lord the king,
        surely one cannot go to the right or to the left from all that my lord the
        king has spoken. Yes, your servant Joab himself commanded me, and he put
        all of these words in the mouth of your servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In order to change the situation, your servant Joab did this thing.
        But my lord has wisdom, as the wisdom of an angel of God, to know all that
        is on the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the king said to Joab, \u201CLook, please, I will grant this
        thing. Go and bring back the young man Absalom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Absalom Returns to Jerusalem'
      title: Absalom Returns to Jerusalem
      number: 22
      content: "Joab fell with his face to the ground and did obeisance. And he blessed
        the king, and he said, \u201CToday your servant knows that I have found favor
        in your eyes, my lord the king, in that the king has granted the request
        of his servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Joab got up and went to Geshur and brought Absalom to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The king said, \u201CLet him go over to his house, and he may not
        see my face.\u201D So Absalom went over to his house, and did not see the
        face of the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'As far as Absalom, there was not a more handsome man in all of Israel
        to admire so much; from the sole of his foot up to his crown, there was no
        physical defect on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When he shaved his head, it would happen every year, which he did
        because it was heavy on him, he would shave it off and weigh the hair of
        his head: two hundred shekels by the king\u2019s weight.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Three sons were born to Absalom and one daughter, whose name was
        Tamar. She was a woman beautiful of appearance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Absalom lived in Jerusalem two full years, but he did not see the
        face of the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So Absalom sent for Joab, in order that he send him to the king,
        but he was not willing to go to him. He sent again a second time, but he
        was not willing to go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So he said to his servants, \u201CLook at the tract of land of Joab
        next to mine, for he has barley plants there. Go, set it ablaze with fire.\u201D
        So the servants of Absalom set the tract of land ablaze with fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Joab got up and went to Absalom, to the house, and said to him,
        \u201CWhy have your servants set my tract of land ablaze with fire?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Absalom said to Joab, \u201CLook, I have sent to you, saying, \u2018Come
        here that I may send you to the king to say, \u201CWhy have I come from Geshur?
        It would be better for me if I were still there.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 So then,
        let me see the face of the king; if there is guilt in me, then let him kill
        me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So Joab went to the king and he told him. Then he summoned Absalom,
        and he came to the king, and he bowed down to him with his face to the ground
        before the king. Then the king kissed Absalom. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Absalom Leads a Rebellion'
      title: Absalom Leads a Rebellion
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened afterward that Absalom made himself a chariot with horses
        and fifty men running before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Absalom used to rise early in the morning, and he stood beside the
        road at the gate; anyone who had a legal dispute to bring to the king for
        judgment Absalom would call to him and say, \u201CWhere are you from?\u201D
        And he would say, \u201CYour servant is from one of the tribes of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Absalom would say to him, \u201CLook, your case is good and
        right, but for you there is no hearing with the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Absalom would say, \u201COh, that someone would appoint me as
        judge in the land, that anyone might come to me who had a legal dispute or
        a case, and I would give him justice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It happened whenever anyone drew near to do obeisance to him, that
        he would stretch his hand and take hold of him and kiss him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Absalom did like this to all of Israel who came to the king for judgment;
        so Absalom stole the hearts of the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "It happened at the end of four years that Absalom said to the king,
        \u201CPlease let me go and pay my vow which I have made to Yahweh in Hebron, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "for your servant made a vow while I was staying in Geshur in Aram,
        saying, \u2018If Yahweh will indeed let me return to Jerusalem, then I will
        worship Yahweh.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the king said to him, \u201CGo in peace.\u201D So he got up
        and went to Hebron. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Absalom sent scouts throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying,
        \u201CWhen you hear the sound of the trumpet, you shall shout \u2018Absalom
        has become king in Hebron!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Two hundred men from Jerusalem went with Absalom as invited guests,
        going in their innocence as they did not know anything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: David Flees from Jerusalem'
      title: David Flees from Jerusalem
      number: 12
      content: 'Absalom sent for Ahithophel the Gilonite, the advisor of David, from
        his city Giloh, while he offered the sacrifices. The conspiracy grew in strength,
        and the people were going and increasing with Absalom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the messenger came to David, saying, \u201CThe hearts of the
        men of Israel have gone after Absalom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then David said to all his servants who were with him in Jerusalem,
        \u201CGet up and let us flee, for there will be no escape for us from Absalom!
        Hurry to go, otherwise he will come quickly and overtake us! And he will
        bring disaster on us and evil! He will attack the city with the edge of the
        sword!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the servants of the king said to the king, \u201CAccording to
        all that my lord the king chooses, your servants are ready to act!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The king went out with all his household following him, but the king
        left behind ten concubines to look after the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the king went out with all the people following him, and they
        stopped at the last house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "All his servants were passing by him: all of the Kerethites and all
        of the Pelethites and all of the Gittites\u2014six hundred men who had followed
        him from Gath\u2014passing before the king.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The king said to Ittai the Gittite, \u201CWhy are you also coming
        with us? Return and stay with the king, for you are a foreigner; moreover,
        you are an exile. You are far from your place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Yesterday when you came and today, I have caused you to wander by
        going with us. Now I am going to where I am going; return and let your brothers
        return. May loyal love and faithfulness be with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But Ittai answered the king and said, \u201CAs Yahweh lives and my
        lord the king lives, surely in the place wherever my lord the king shall
        be, if for death or if for life, surely there your servant will be.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then David said to Ittai, \u201CGo and pass over.\u201D So Ittai
        the Gittite passed over and all his men and all of the little children who
        were with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The Priests Offer Sacrifices for David'
      title: The Priests Offer Sacrifices for David
      number: 23
      content: 'All of the land was weeping with a loud voice as all the people were
        passing by and the king was crossing through the Wadi Kidron, and all the
        people were passing on the road to the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Suddenly Zadok was there, and all of the Levites with him, carrying
        the ark of the covenant of God. They set the ark of God down, and Abiathar
        offered sacrifices until all the people passed out of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The king said to Zadok, \u201CLet the ark of God return to the city.
        If I find favor in the eyes of Yawheh, he will let me return and let me see
        him in his dwelling place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But if he says, \u2018I take no pleasure in you,\u2019 then I am
        ready. Let him do to me that which is good in his eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the king said to Zadok the priest, \u201CAre you a seer? Return
        to the city in peace, with Ahimaaz your son and Jonathan the son of Abiathar,
        your two sons with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "See, I am waiting at the fords of the wilderness until a word comes
        from you all to inform me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Hushai Offers to Serve King David'
      title: Hushai Offers to Serve King David
      number: 29
      content: 'So Zadok and Abiathar returned the ark of God to Jerusalem and they
        remained there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now David was going up on the Ascent of the Olives, weeping as he
        went, with his head covered and going barefoot. All the people who were with
        him each covered their head and wept as they went.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Now David was told, \u201CAhithophel was among the conspirators with
        Absalom.\u201D Then David said, \u201CPlease frustrate the counsel of Ahithophel,
        O Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'It happened that as David was coming up to the summit where he used
        to worship God, suddenly Hushai the Arkite was there to meet him. His coat
        was torn and dirt was on his head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "David said to him, \u201CIf you move on with me, you will be a burden
        to me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "but if you want to return to the city and say to Absalom, \u2018I
        am your servant, O king. I used to be a servant of your father, but from
        then and now I will be your servant,\u2019 then you can frustrate the counsel
        of Ahithophel for me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Will not Zadok and Abiathar the priests be with you there? It shall
        be that all the words you hear from the house of the king you shall tell
        Zadok and Abiathar the priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Look, there with them are their two sons, Ahimaaz of Zadok and Jonathan
        of Abiathar. You shall send to me by means of them all the words that you
        hear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So Hushai the friend of David came to the city as Absalom was entering
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ziba Brings Provisions'
      title: Ziba Brings Provisions
      number: 1
      content: 'Now David passed a little from beyond the summit, and suddenly Ziba
        the servant of Mephibosheth was there to meet him with a pair of saddled
        donkeys; on them were two hundred loaves of bread and a hundred raisin cakes,
        with a hundred summer fruits and a skin of wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The king said to Ziba, \u201CWhat do you want to accomplish by bringing
        these?\u201D And Ziba said, \u201CThe donkeys are for the king\u2019s household
        to ride on; the bread and the summer fruit are for the young men to eat,
        and the wine is for the faint in the wilderness to drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CWhere is the son of your lord?\u201D And
        Ziba said to the king, \u201CHe is living in Jerusalem for he said, \u2018Today
        the house of Israel shall return the kingdom of my father to me.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Shimei Curses David'
      title: Shimei Curses David
      number: 4
      content: "The king said to Ziba, \u201CLook, all that was Mephibosheth\u2019s
        is yours.\u201D Ziba said, \u201CI hereby do obeisance; may I find favor
        in your eyes, my lord the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'King David came up to Bahurim and suddenly a man from there was coming
        out from the family of the house of Saul, and his name was Shimei the son
        of Gera. He was cursing as he came out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he threw stones at David and at all the servants of King David
        and at all the people and at all the mighty warriors on his right and on
        his left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Shimei said while cursing him, \u201CGo out, go out, you man of bloodshed,
        you man of wickedness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Yahweh has returned on you all the blood of the household of Saul
        whom you have supplanted as king, and Yahweh has given the kingship into
        the hand of Absalom your son. Look, you are in disaster for you are a man
        of blood.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Abishai the son of Zeruiah said to the king, \u201CWhy should
        this dead dog curse my lord the king? Please let me go over and take off
        his head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The king said, \u201CWhat do we have in common, sons of Zeruiah?
        If he curses because Yahweh has said to him \u2018Curse David,\u2019 who
        can say, \u201CWhy have you done this?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "David said to Abishai and to all his servants, \u201CLook, my son
        who came out of my loins is seeking my life. Now as far as this Benjaminite,
        leave him alone and let him curse, for Yahweh has spoken to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Perhaps Yahweh will look in my eye and repay good for me in place
        of his curse this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then David and his men went on the road, with Shimei going on the
        side of the hill beside him, cursing as he went. He threw stones beside him
        and threw dust in the air. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Hushai Comes to Absalom'
      title: Hushai Comes to Absalom
      number: 14
      content: 'When the king and all of the people who were with him arrived, he
        was weary, so he recovered there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now Absalom and all the people, the men of Israel, had come to Jerusalem,
        and Ahithophel was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When Hushai the Arkite the friend of David came to Absalom, Hushai
        said to Absalom, \u201CLong live the king, long live the king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Absalom said to Hushai, \u201CThis is your loyal love with your friend?
        Why did you not go with your friend?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Hushai said to Absalom, \u201CNo, rather, whom Yahweh and this
        people and all the men of Israel have chosen, to him I will be, and with
        him I will remain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Furthermore, for whom have I served? Is it not in the presence of
        his son that I have served before your father? So shall I serve you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Absalom said to Ahithophel, \u201CGive your advice. What shall
        we do?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Ahithophel said to Absalom, \u201CGo to the concubines of your
        father whom he left behind to watch over the house, then all of Israel will
        hear that you made yourself odious to your father, and all of your followers
        will be motivated!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then they pitched a tent for Absalom on the roof, and he went in
        to the concubines of his father before the eyes of all Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The counsel that Ahithophel gave in those days was regarded as when
        a man inquired of the word of God, so all the counsel of Ahithophel was esteemed
        both by David and by Absalom. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hushai Frustrates the Counsel of Ahithophel'
      title: Hushai Frustrates the Counsel of Ahithophel
      number: 1
      content: "Then Ahithophel said to Absalom, \u201CPlease let me choose twelve
        thousand men, and I will set out and pursue after David tonight.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will come upon him while he is weary and weak. I will startle him,
        and all of the people who are with him will flee. Then I will strike down
        the king while he is alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then I will return all the people to you; when all have returned,
        the man whom you are seeking will be dead, but all the people will be safe.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The word was right in the eyes of Absalom and in the eyes of all
        the elders of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Absalom said, \u201CPlease call also for Hushai the Arkite,
        and let us hear what he has to say also.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Hushai came to Absalom, who said to him, \u201CShall we do according
        to this word that Ahithophel has spoken? If not, then you tell us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Hushai said to Absalom, \u201CThe counsel that Ahithophel gave
        is not good at this time.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Hushai continued, \u201CYou know your father and his men, that they
        are mighty warriors and they are enraged as a bear robbed of her offspring
        in the field. Your father is a man of war, so he will not spend the night
        with the troops. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now he has hidden himself in one of the caves or in one of the places.
        At the moment he falls on them the first time, whoever hears the report will
        say, \u2018There has been a defeat among the people who follow after Absalom.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And he is also a valiant warrior, whose heart is like the heart of
        the lion. He will certainly melt with fear, for all Israel knows that your
        father is a mighty warrior and those who are with him are valiant warriors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I give the advice that all of Israel from Dan to Beersheba should
        be completely gathered to you, as the sand which is on the seashore for abundance,
        with you personally going into the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then we will come to him in one of the places where he may be found,
        and we shall come upon him as the dew falls on the ground. He and all the
        men who are with him will not survive, not even one! '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Even if he withdraws to a city, all Israel will bring up ropes to
        that city, and they will drag him away to the valley until there is not even
        a pebble to be found.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Hushai Sends Word to David'
      title: Hushai Sends Word to David
      number: 14
      content: "Then Absalom and all the men of Israel said, \u201CThe advice of
        Hushai the Arkite is better than the advice of Ahithophel.\u201D (Now Yahweh
        had ordained to frustrate the good counsel of Ahithophel in order for Yahweh
        to bring misery upon Absalom). "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Hushai said to Zadok and to Abiathar the priests, \u201CThus and
        so Ahithophel advised Absalom and the elders of Israel, but thus and so I
        have advised. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So then, send quickly and tell David, \u2018Don\u2019t spend the
        night at the fords of the wilderness! Moreover, by all means cross over lest
        the king and all the people who are with him be swallowed up.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now Jonathan and Ahimaaz were staying at En Rogel, so a servant girl
        used to go and tell them, then they would go and tell King David, for they
        were not able to be seen coming to the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But a young man saw them and told Absalom, so both of them went quickly
        and came to the house of a man at Bahurim. Now he had a well in his courtyard,
        so they went down there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the woman took and spread a covering over the opening of the
        well; then she spread out dried grain on it, so nothing was discovered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When the servants of Absalom came to the woman at the house, they
        said, \u201CWhere are Ahimaaz and Jonathan?\u201D And she said to them, \u201CThey
        crossed over the brook of water.\u201D So they searched but could not find
        them, so they returned to Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "After they left, they came up from the well and went and told King
        David. They said to David, \u201CSet out and cross over the water quickly,
        for thus Ahithophel has advised against you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So David and all the people who were with him set out, and they crossed
        over the Jordan until morning light until there was no one missing who had
        not crossed over the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When Ahithophel saw that his advice was not followed, he saddled
        the donkey, and he set out and went up to his house in his city. After he
        set his house in order, he hanged himself, and he died and was buried in
        the tomb of his ancestors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now David had come to Mahanaim, and Absalom had crossed over the
        Jordan, he and all the men of Israel with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Absalom had appointed Amasa in place of Joab over the army. Now Amasa
        was the son of a man whose name was Ithra the Israelite, who had married
        Abigail the daughter of Nahash the sister of Zeruiah, the mother of Joab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Israel and Absalom camped in the land of Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Just as David had arrived in Mahanaim, Shobi the son of Nahash from
        Rabbah of the Ammonites and Makir the son of Ammiel from Lo Debar and Barzillai
        the Gileadite from Rogelim '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'brought beds and basins and objects of pottery, as well as wheat,
        barley, flour, roasted grain, beans, lentils, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "honey, curds, sheep, cheese, and cattle for David and for the people
        who were with him to eat. For they had thought, \u201CThe troops are hungry
        and weary and thirsty in the wilderness.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Absalom Dies in Battle'
      title: Absalom Dies in Battle
      number: 1
      content: 'Then David mustered the people who were with him, and he appointed
        over them commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David sent forth a third of the troops under the command of Joab,
        and a third under the command of Abishai, the brother of Joab, the son of
        Zeruiah, and the remaining third under the command of Ittai the Gittite.
        And the king said to the troops, \u201CI, even I, will certainly go out with
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the troops said, \u201CYou will not go out, for if we must flee,
        then they will not care about us; even if half of us die, they will not care
        about us, but now, you are like ten thousand of us. And so then, it is better
        for us that you be in the city to help.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The king said to them, \u201CI will do what seems good in your eyes.\u201D
        So the king stood at the side of the gate while all of the troops went out
        by hundreds and by thousands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The king ordered Joab, Abishai, and Ittai, \u201CWith respect to
        the young man Absalom, deal gently for me.\u201D And all the troops heard
        when the king ordered all of the commanders concerning the matter of Absalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The army went out to the field to meet Israel, and the battle was
        fought in the forest of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The army of Israel was defeated there before the servants of David,
        and the defeat there was great on that day: twenty thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The battle there was spreading over the surface of all the land,
        and the forest devoured more among the army than the sword did on that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Absalom was found in the presence of the servants of David as he
        was riding on the mule. The mule went under the thicket of the great oak
        tree, and his head was caught in the tree. He was left hanging between heaven
        and earth, and the mule which was under him went on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When a certain man saw it, he told Joab, and he said, \u201CLook,
        I saw Absalom hanging in the oak tree!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Joab said to the man who was telling him, \u201CLook, if you
        saw, why did you not strike him down to the ground there? I would have gladly
        given you ten pieces of silver and a leather belt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The man said to Joab, \u201CEven if I felt the weight of a thousand
        pieces of silver in my palms, I would not have sent my hand against the son
        of the king, for in our ears the king commanded you and Abishai and Ittai,
        \u2018Whoever you may be, protect the young man Absalom.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "If I had dealt treacherously against his life, and there is not any
        matter hidden from the king, you would have presented yourself aloof.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Joab said, \u201CNo longer will I wait in your presence.\u201D Then
        he took three spears in his hand and thrust them into the heart of Absalom
        while he was still alive in the oak tree. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then ten of the young men who bore the weapons of Joab surrounded
        him and struck and killed Absalom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Joab blew on the trumpet and the troops returned from pursuing
        after Israel, for Joab kept back the troops. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They took Absalom and they threw him into the large pit in the forest
        and raised a very great heap of stones over him. Then all of Israel fled,
        each to his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "(Now Absalom had taken and set up for himself in his lifetime a stone
        pillar that is in the valley of the king, because he said, \u201CI have no
        son in order to remember my name,\u201D and he called the stone pillar by
        his name. It is called the monument of Absalom until this day). "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said, \u201CPlease let me run and bring
        the good news to the king that Yahweh has vindicated him from the hand of
        his enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Joab said to him, \u201CYou will not be a man bringing good news
        this day! You may bring good news on another day, but today you will not
        be bringing good news because the king\u2019s son is dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Joab said to the Cushite, \u201CGo, tell the king what you have
        seen\u201D; then the Cushite bowed down to Joab and ran off. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok again said to Joab, \u201CCome what
        may, please let me also run after the Cushite.\u201D Joab asked, \u201CWhy
        are you wanting to run, my son, when for you there is no messenger\u2019s
        reward?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CCome what may, I want to run.\u201D He said to him, \u201CRun,\u201D
        so Ahimaaz ran on the road on the plain, and he passed the Cushite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now David was sitting between the two gates, and the sentinel went
        up to the roof of the gate by the wall and he lifted up his eyes and watched,
        and look, a man was running by himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The sentry called and told the king, and the king said, \u201CIf
        he is alone, good news is in his mouth.\u201D He kept coming closer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the sentinel saw another man running, so the sentinel called
        to the gatekeeper and said, \u201CLook, a man running alone.\u201D The king
        said, \u201CThis one also is bringing good news.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The sentinel said, \u201CI am seeing that the running of the first
        is like the running of Ahimaaz the son of Zakok.\u201D The king said, \u201CHe
        is a good man; he will come, for good news.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Ahimaaz called and said to the king, \u201CPeace.\u201D He bowed
        down to the king with his face to the ground, and he said, \u201CMay Yahweh
        your God be blessed, who has delivered the men who raised their hand against
        my lord the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The king said, \u201CIs it peace for the young man Absalom?\u201D
        Ahimaaz said, \u201CI saw the great commotion when Joab the servant of the
        king sent your servant, but I do not know what it was all about.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CTurn aside, take your place here,\u201D
        so he turned aside and waited. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Suddenly the Cushite arrived and said, \u201CMay my lord the king
        receive the good news, for Yahweh has vindicated you today from the power
        of all who stood up against you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The king said to the Cushite, \u201CIs it peace for the young man
        Absalom?\u201D Then the Cushite answered, \u201CMay the enemies of my lord
        the king and all who rise up against you to harm you be like the young man!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: " The king was upset, and he went up to the upper room of the gate
        and wept. He said as he went, \u201CMy son, Absalom, my son, my son, Absalom.
        If only I had died instead of you, Absalom, my son, my son.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: King David Weeps for Absalom'
      title: King David Weeps for Absalom
      number: 1
      content: 'And it was told to Joab that the king was weeping and he mourned
        over Absalom, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "so the victory turned to mourning on that day for all the army, because
        they had heard that day, \u201CThe king is grieving over his son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The army came secretly into the city on that day because the army
        was disgraced when they fled in the battle, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and because the king had covered his face and cried with a loud voice,
        \u201CMy son, Absalom, Absalom, my son, my son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Joab came to the king\u2019s house and said, \u201CToday you
        have humiliated the faces of all of your servants who have saved your life
        this day, and the life of your sons and your daughters, the life of your
        wives, and the life of your concubines, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'by loving those who hate you and hating those who love you. Indeed,
        you have made clear this day that you have no regard for your commanders
        or officers, for I have realized today that were Absalom alive, and all of
        us were dead, then that would have been right in your eyes! '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So then, get up and go out and speak kindly to your servants, for
        I swear by Yahweh, if you do not go out, no man will lodge this night with
        you, and this disaster will be greater for you than any disaster that has
        come upon you from your childhood until now!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: David Returns from Exile'
      title: David Returns from Exile
      number: 8
      content: "So the king got up and he sat in the gate, and they told all the
        army, \u201CLook, the king is sitting in the gate.\u201D Then all the army
        came before the king; whereas all of Israel had fled, each to his tent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then it happened that all the people were disputing among all the
        tribes of Israel, saying, \u201CThe king delivered us from the hand of our
        enemies, and he saved us from the hand of the Philistines, but now he has
        fled from the land because of Absalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now Absalom whom we anointed as king over us has died in the battle;
        so then, why are you taking no action to restore the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then King David sent to Zadok and to Abiathar the priests, saying,
        \u201CSpeak to the elders of Judah: \u2018Why are you last to bring back
        the king to his house? The talk of all Israel has come to the king in his
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "My brothers, you are my bones and you are my flesh. Why should you
        be the last to bring back the king?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "To Amasa you shall say: \u2018Are you not my bones and my flesh?
        May God punish me if you are not the commander of my army before me forever,
        in place of Joab.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So he turned the heart of all the men of Judah as one man, and they
        sent word to the king, \u201CReturn, you and all your servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the king returned and he came to the Jordan; Judah had come
        to Gilgal to come to meet the king, to bring the king over the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Shimei the son of Gera, the son of the Benjaminite, who was
        from Bahurim quickly came down with the men of Judah to meet King David, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and a thousand men were with him from Benjamin. Too, Ziba the servant
        of the household of Saul and fifteen of his sons and twenty of his servants
        were with him, and they rushed to the Jordan before the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The crossing took place to bring the household of the king over and
        to do good in his eyes. Then Shimei the son of Gera fell before the king
        when he crossed over the Jordan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and he said to the king, \u201CMay not my lord hold me guilty, and
        may you not remember how your servant did wrong on the day that my lord the
        king went out from Jerusalem, by taking it to heart! "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For your servant knows that I have sinned; look, I have come this
        day as the first of all the house of Joseph to come down to meet my lord
        the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Abishai the son of Zeruiah responded and said, \u201CBecause
        of this, should not Shimei be put to death, for he cursed the anointed one
        of Yahweh?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then David said, \u201CWhat is it to me or to you, sons of Zeruiah,
        that you should be an adversary today? Should anyone be put to death in Israel?
        Do I not know today that I am king over Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then the king said to Shimei, \u201CYou shall not die,\u201D and
        so the king swore to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now, Mephibosheth the son of Saul came down to meet the king; he
        had not taken care of his feet nor trimmed his moustache nor washed his clothes
        from the day the king left until the day he came back in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "It happened that when he came to Jerusalem to meet the king, the
        king said to him, \u201CWhy did you not come with me, Mephibosheth?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then he said, \u201CMy lord the king, my servant deceived me, for
        your servant had said, \u2018Let me saddle the donkey that I may ride on
        her and go with the king,\u2019 for your servant is lame. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But he slandered against your servant to my lord the king. My lord
        the king is like the angel of God; do as you see fit..\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For there was no one in all the house of my father who were not doomed
        to death before my lord the king, but you set your servant among those who
        eat at your table. Do I have any righteousness any longer except to cry out
        to the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then the king said to him, \u201CWhy should you speak any more about
        the matter? I have decided: you and Ziba shall divide the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Mephibosheth said to the king, \u201CLet him take the whole
        thing, since my lord the king has come safely to his house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then Barzillai the Gileadite came down from Rogelim and crossed with
        the king over the Jordan to escort him through the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now Barzillai was very old, eighty years old. Now he had provided
        the king with food while he was staying at Mahanaim, for he was a very wealthy
        man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The king said to Barzillai, \u201CYou cross over with me, and I will
        provide for you to dwell with me in Jerusalem.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then Barzillai said to the king, \u201CWhat are the days of the years
        of my life, that I should go with the king to Jerusalem? "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'I am eighty years old today. Can I discern between good and bad?
        Or can your servant taste what I eat or what I drink? Or can I still hear
        the voice of singing men and women? Why should your servant be a burden any
        longer to my lord the king? '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Your servant shall go over the Jordan with the king a little way,
        but why should the king recompense me with this reward? '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Please let your servant return, and let me die in my city in the
        tomb of my father and my mother. Here is your servant Kimham; let him cross
        over with my lord the king, and do for him that which is good in your eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "The king said, \u201CLet Kimham go over with me, and I will do for
        him the good in your eyes, and all that you desire of me I will do for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Then all the people crossed over the Jordan, and the king crossed
        and kissed Barzillai and blessed him; then he returned to his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The king went over to Gilgal, and Kimham went over with him. All
        the people of Judah went over with the king, and half of the people of Israel
        too. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Suddenly, all the men of Israel were coming to the king. They said
        to the king, \u201CWhy have our brothers the men of Judah stolen away and
        brought the king and his household over the Jordan, with all the men of David?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then all the men of Judah answered the men of Israel, \u201CBecause
        the king is my close relative! Why are you this angry over this matter? Have
        we by any means eaten anything from the king? Did we take by any means anything
        that was not ours?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then the people of Israel answered the men of Judah and said, \u201CI
        have ten times as much in the king, moreover in David I have more than you.
        Why did you treat me with contempt by not giving me first chance to bring
        back my king?\u201D But the words of the men of Judah were fiercer than the
        word of the men of Israel. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sheba Leads a Revolt'
      title: Sheba Leads a Revolt
      number: 1
      content: "Now a man of wickedness was found there whose name was Sheba the
        son of Bichri, a Benjaminite. He blew the horn and said, \u201CThere is no
        share for us in David, and there is no inheritance for us in the son of Jesse;
        each to his tents, O Israel!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then all the men of Israel went up from following after David, following
        instead after Sheba the son of Bicri, but the men of Judah stuck to their
        king from the Jordan up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Joab Assassinates Amasa'
      title: Joab Assassinates Amasa
      number: 3
      content: 'David went up to his house in Jerusalem, then the king took the ten
        concubines whom he had left to look after the house, and he put them under
        confinement. However, he provided for them, but he did not sleep with them.
        So they were confined until the day of their death, like a lifetime of widowhood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king said to Amasa, \u201CSummon for me the men of Judah
        within three days, and be here yourself.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Amasa went to summon Judah, but he tarried more than the appointed
        time which he had set for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then David said to Abishai, \u201CNow Sheba the son of Bicri will
        do us more harm than Absalom. You take the servants of your lord and pursue
        after him, lest he find fortified cities for himself and escape from us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the men of Joab, the Kerethites and the Pelethites, and all
        the mighty warriors went out after him; they went out from Jerusalem to pursue
        after Sheba the son of Bicri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They were near the big rock that is in Gibeon, and Amasa came before
        them. Joab was dressed in his military clothing, with a utility belt on him
        and a sword strapped to his waist in its scabbard. Now he went out, and it
        fell out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Joab said to Amasa, \u201CIs it peace, O you my brother?\u201D
        Then the right hand of Joab took hold of the beard of Amasa as if to kiss
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now Amasa was not on his guard against the sword that was in Joab\u2019s
        hand, and he struck him with it into the stomach, and his entrails poured
        out to the ground. He did not strike him again, and he died. Then Joab and
        Abishai his brother pursued after Sheba the son of Bicri. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "A young man stood over him, from the young men of Joab, and he said,
        \u201CWhoever takes delight in Joab and whoever is for David, follow after
        Joab.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now Amasa was wallowing in the blood in the middle of the highway;
        when the man saw that all the people stood there, he turned Amasa over from
        the highway into the field, and he threw a garment over him because he had
        seen that all who had come by him had stopped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Wisdom from a Woman under Siege'
      title: Wisdom from a Woman under Siege
      number: 13
      content: 'After he was removed from the highway, all the men passed by after
        Joab to pursue after Sheba the son of Bicri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '(He had passed through all the tribes of Israel to Abel and Beth
        Maacah; now all of the Berites had been treated badly, so they also followed
        after him.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they came and besieged him in Abel Beth Maacah. They threw up
        a siege ramp against the city, and they stood against the ramparts. And all
        the army who were with Joab were battering to cause the wall to fall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then a wise woman from the city called out, \u201CListen, listen!
        Please speak to Joab to come near here so that I may speak to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he came near to her, and the woman asked, \u201CAre you Joab?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CI am.\u201D Then she said to him, \u201CListen to the
        words of your servant.\u201D He said, \u201CI am listening.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then she said, \u201CIn former times, they would always say, \u2018By
        all means, let them inquire in Abel,\u2019 and so they settled things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I am one of the faithful representatives of Israel. You are seeking
        to destroy a city and a mother in Israel. Why do you want to swallow the
        inheritance of Yahweh?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Joab answered and said, \u201CFar be it, far be it from me that
        I should swallow or I should destroy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "That is not the matter. But a man from the mountains of Ephraim,
        whose name is Sheba the son Bicri, has lifted up his hand against the king,
        against David. Give only him to us, and I will depart from the city.\u201D
        The woman said to Joab, \u201CLook, his head is being thrown down to you
        over the wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The woman went to all of the people with her wise plan, so they cut
        off the head of Sheba the son of Bicri and threw it to Joab. Then he blew
        the horn and dispersed from the city, each to his tent. Then Joab returned
        to Jerusalem to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now Joab was over all the army of Israel and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada
        was over the Carites and over the Pelethites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Adoram was over the forced labor, and Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud
        was the recorder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Shiya was secretary, and Zadok and Abiathar were priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Also Ira the Jairite was priest for David. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Famine Brings Justice'
      title: The Famine Brings Justice
      number: 1
      content: "There was a famine in the days of David for three years, year after
        year. And David inquired of Yahweh, and Yahweh said, \u201CThe bloodguilt
        is on Saul and on his household, because he killed the Gibeonites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the king called the Gibeonites and spoke to them. Now the Gibeonites
        were not from the Israelites; they were from the remainder of the Amorites.
        Now the Israelites had sworn to them, but Saul tried to wipe them out in
        his zeal for the Israelites and Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So David asked the Gibeonites, \u201CWhat can I do for you, and with
        what can I make amends that you may bless the inheritance of Yahweh?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Gibeonites said to him, \u201CIt is not a matter for us
        of silver or gold with Saul or with his household. It is not for us to put
        to death anyone in Israel.\u201D He asked, \u201CWhat are you saying that
        I should do for you all?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then they said to the king, \u201CThe man who consumed us and who
        plotted against us so that we were destroyed from existing in all of the
        territory of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "let seven men from his sons be given over to us, and we will execute
        them before Yahweh in Gibeah of Saul, the chosen one of Yahweh.\u201D Then
        the king said, \u201CI will give them over.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But the king spared Mephibosheth the son of Jonathan, the son of
        Saul, because of the sworn oath of Yahweh which was between them, between
        David and Jonathan the son of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the king took two of the sons of Rizpah the daughter of Aiah,
        whom she bore to Saul, namely Armoni and Mephibosheth, and five of the sons
        of Michal the daughter of Saul whom she had borne to Adriel the son of Barzillai
        the Meholathite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He gave them into the hands of the Gibeonites, and they executed
        them on the mountain in the presence of Yahweh, and the seven fell together.
        Now they were put to death in the days of the harvest, at the beginning of
        the harvest of barley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Rizpah the daughter of Aiah took the sackcloth, and she spread it
        for herself on the rock at the beginning of the harvest until water gushed
        forth on them from heaven, but she did not allow the birds of heaven to rest
        on them by day nor the animals of the field by night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'David was told about what Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, the concubine
        of Saul, had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So David left and took the bones of Saul and the bones of Jonathan
        his son from the rulers of Jabesh Gilead, who had stolen them from the public
        square of Beth Shan, where the Philistines hung them when the Philistines
        killed Saul on Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He brought up the bones of Saul and the bones of Jonathan his son
        from there, and they gathered the bones of the executed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Battles with the Philistines Recounted'
      title: Battles with the Philistines Recounted
      number: 14
      content: 'And they buried the bones of Saul and Jonathan his son in the land
        of Benjamin at Zela, in the tomb of Kish his father. They did all that the
        king had commanded, and afterward God was entreated for the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'There was war again for the Philistines with Israel, and David and
        his servants with him went down, and they fought the Philistines, and David
        grew weary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now Yishbi in Nob, who was among the descendents of Raphah (now the
        weight of his spearhead was three hundredweight of bronze, and he was newly
        armed), said that he would kill David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But Abishai the son of Zeruiah helped him, and he attacked the Philistine
        and killed him. Then the men of David swore to him, saying, \u201CYou shall
        not go out with us any longer to the battle, so that you do not quench the
        lamp of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'It happened afterward that there was again battle at Gob with the
        Philistines. Then Sibbecai the Hushathite killed Saph who was among the descendants
        of the Raphah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'There was again a battle with the Philistines at Gob. And Elhanan
        the son of Jaare-Oregim, the Bethlehemite, killed Goliath the Gittite, the
        shaft of whose spear was like the beam of a weaver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Once again there was battle at Gath, and there was a man of great
        size. The fingers of his hand and the toes of his feet were six and six,
        twenty-four in number. He was also born to the Raphah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He taunted Israel but Jonathan the son of Shimei, the brother of
        David, killed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'These four were born for the Raphah in Gath, and they fell by the
        hand of David and by the hand of his servants. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Victory Song of David'
      title: The Victory Song of David
      number: 1
      content: 'Then David spoke to Yahweh the words of this song, on the day Yahweh
        delivered him from the hand of all his enemies and from the hand of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said: \u201CYahweh is my rock, my fortress, and my deliverer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I take refuge in God, my rock, my shield, and the strength of my
        salvation. My stronghold and my refuge, O my savior, you will save me from
        violence! '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I call upon Yahweh who is praiseworthy, and I am saved from those
        who hate me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For the breaker waves of death engulfed me; the currents of chaos
        overwhelmed me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The ropes of Sheol entangled me; the snares of death confronted me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In my distress I called upon Yahweh, and to my God I called. He heard
        my voice from his temple, and my cry for help was to his ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The earth heaved and shook, the foundations of heaven trembled and
        heaved because he was angry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Smoke went up from his nostrils and fire from his mouth. Burning
        coals devoured, they burned from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He bowed the heavens and came down; a very thick cloud was under
        his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He rode upon a cherub and flew; he was seen on the wings of the wind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He put darkness as a canopy all around him, a collection of thick
        rain clouds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'From the brightness before him flamed burning coals of fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Yahweh thundered from heaven, and the Most High uttered his voice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He sent arrows and he scattered them, lightning, and he directed
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the channels of water of the sea were exposed, the foundations
        of the world, at the rebuke of Yawheh, from the blast of the breath of his
        nostrils. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He sent from a high position and took me; he drew me from mighty
        waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He delivered me from my strong enemies, from those who hate me, for
        they were mightier than I. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They approached me on the day of my disaster, but Yahweh was my support. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He brought me out to a spacious place. He delivered me because he
        delighted in me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yahweh rewarded me according to my righteousness, according to the
        cleanness of my hands he recompensed me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For I have kept the ways of Yahweh; I have not acted wickedly against
        my God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For all of his ordinances were before me, and I did not turn aside
        from his statutes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I was blameless before him, and I kept myself from my iniquity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Yahweh has recompensed me according to my righteousness, according
        to my cleanness before his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'With the loyal, you act as loyal, and with the blameless, you show
        yourself blameless. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'With the pure, you show yourself pure, but with the crooked, you
        appear as a fool. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Humble people you will deliver, but your eyes are on the haughty,
        whom you bring down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For you, O Yahweh are my lamp, and Yahweh lightens my darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'For by you I can run a raid; by my God I can leap over a wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'This God, his way is blameless; the promise of Yahweh is flawless.
        He is a shield to all who take refuge in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For who is God apart from Yahweh? And who is a rock apart from our
        God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'God is my strong refuge, he has fully opened my way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'He makes my feet like a doe deer, and on my high places he has set
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'He trains my hands for the war, so that my arms can bend a bow of
        bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'You have given me the shield of your salvation; your willingness
        to help has made me great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'You have broadened my steps beneath me; my ankles have not wobbled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'I pursued those who hate me, and I destroyed them. I did not turn
        back until finishing them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'I wiped them out and I smashed them; they did not get up; they fell
        under my feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'You have girded me with physical strength for the battle; you caused
        those who rose up against me to kneel under me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'My enemies you cause to retreat from me;  I destroy those who hate
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'They looked out, but there was no deliverer, even to Yahweh, but
        he did not answer them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'I beat them fine, like the dust of the earth; like the mire of the
        streets, I crushed them, I stamped them down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'You delivered me from the strife of my people; you preserved me as
        the head of the nations. A people I had not known served me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Children of a foreign land came cringing to me; when they heard of
        me, they became obedient to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Children of a foreign land lost heart and came trembling from their
        strongholds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Yahweh lives! Blessed be my rock! May God, the rock of my salvation,
        be exalted! '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'God does vengeance for me, bringing down peoples under me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'He brings me out from my enemies, and from those who rose up against
        me you lift me up, and from men of violence you rescue me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Therefore I will extol you, Yahweh, among the nations! I will sing
        praises to your name! '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "He makes great salvation for his king and shows loyal love to his
        anointed one, David and to his descendants forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Extols Yahweh'
      title: David Extols Yahweh
      number: 1
      content: 'These are the last words of David, the declaration of David the son
        of Jesse, and the declaration of the man exalted by the Most High, the anointed
        one of the God of Jacob and the darling of the songs of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThe spirit of Yahweh speaks through me, and his word is upon
        my tongue. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The God of Israel said to me, the rock of Israel has spoken; \u2018He
        who rules over mankind rules righteously, in the fear of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Like the light of the morning when the sun rises, shining with no
        clouds, bringing vegetation from the earth apart from rain.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yet not so is my house with God, for he made an everlasting covenant
        for me, arranging everything. He has secured all my deliverance, and all
        my desire he will cause to happen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But evil persons are like thorns cast aside; all of them, because
        they cannot be picked up in the hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: David\u2019s Faithful Soldiers"
      title: "David\u2019s Faithful Soldiers"
      number: 7
      content: "And if a man wants to touch them, he must use an iron instrument
        or the shaft of a spear; then they are consumed entirely with fire on the
        spot.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "These are the names of the mighty warriors who were David\u2019s:
        Josheb-Basshebeth a Tahkemonite was chief of three officers; first Adino,
        whose spear was against eight hundred slain on one occurrence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Next to him Eleazar, the son of Dodo the son of an Ahohite, was among
        the three mighty warriors with David when they defied the Philistines and
        they gathered there for the battle and the men of Israel withdrew. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He stood up and struck down the Philistines until his hand grew tired
        and his hand clung to the sword, and Yahweh brought about a great victory
        on that day. Then the army returned back to him only for stripping the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Next to him was Shamma, the son of Agee the Hararite. When the Philistines
        assembled at Lehi, a plot of the field was there filled with lentils, and
        the army fled there from the presence of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But he took a stand in the middle of the plot of land and defended
        it. He killed the Philistines, and Yahweh brought about a great victory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then three of the thirty leaders went down and came to David at the
        time of the harvest to the cave of Adullam, while a group of the Philistines
        were camping in the valley of the Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now at that time, David was in the stronghold, and a garrison of
        the Philistines was in Bethlehem at that same time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "David said longingly, \u201COh that someone would bring me a drink
        of water from the well of Bethlehem that is at the gate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So three of the mighty warriors broke into the camp of the Philistines,
        and they drew water from the well of Bethlehem that was at the gate, and
        they carried it and brought it to David. But he was not willing to drink
        it, but poured it out to Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He said, \u201CFar be it from me before Yahweh that I should do this.
        Is this not the blood of the men who went at the risk of their lives?\u201D
        So he was not willing to drink it. These things the three mighty warriors
        did. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now Abishai the brother of Joab the son of Zeruiah was himself the
        leader of the thirty. He was wielding his spear against three hundred slain
        and gained a name among the thirty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Among the thirty, is it not that he was honored and became a commander
        for them? But he did not come up to the three. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of Ish-Hai, was a great man
        of deeds from Kabzeel. He struck down two sons of Ariel of Moab, and he went
        down and killed a lion in the middle of a pit on a snowy day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He also killed a good-looking Egyptian man, in whose hand was a spear.
        He went down against him with the staff and snatched the spear from the hand
        of the Egyptian and killed him with his spear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'These things Benaiah the son of Jehoiada did and gained a name for
        himself among the three mighty warriors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The Mighty Men of David'
      title: The Mighty Men of David
      number: 23
      content: 'He was honored more than the thirty, but he did not come up to the
        three. David appointed him in charge of his bodyguard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Among the thirty were Asahel the brother of Joab, Elhanan the son
        of Dodo of Bethlehem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Shammah the Harodite, Elika the Harodite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Abiezer the Anathothite, Mebunnai the Hushathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Zalmon the Ahohite, Maharai the Netophathite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Heleb the son of Baanah the Netophathite, Ittai the son of Ribai
        from Gibeah of the sons of Benjamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Benaiah the Pirathonite, Hiddai from the wadis of Gaash, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Abi-Albon the Arbathite, Azmaveth the Barhumite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Eliahba the Shaalbonite, the sons of Jashen, Jonathan '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'the son of Shammah the Hararite, Ahiam the son of Sharar the Ararite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Eliphelet the son of Ahasbai the son of the Maacathite, Eliam the
        son of Ahithophel the Gilonite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Hezro the Carmelite, Paarai the Arbite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Igal the son of Nathan from Zobah, Bani the Gadite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Beerothite, the carriers of the weapons
        of Joab the son of Zeruiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Uriah the Hittite; in all, thirty-seven. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David and the Census of the People'
      title: David and the Census of the People
      number: 1
      content: "Again Yahweh was angry with Israel, and he incited David against
        them, saying, \u201CGo count Israel and Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The king said to Joab, the commander of the army who was with him:
        \u201CPlease go about through all the tribes of Israel from Dan to Beersheba,
        and count the people that I may know the number of the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Joab said to the king, \u201CMay Yahweh your God increase the
        people a hundred times what they are as the eyes of my lord the king are
        seeing. But my lord the king, why does he desire this thing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the word of the king prevailed over Joab and over the commanders
        of the army, so Joab and the commanders of the army went out from before
        the king to count the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They crossed over the Jordan and camped at Aroer to the south of
        the city, which was in the middle of the wadi of Gad, and up to Jazer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then they went to Gilead and to the land of Tahtim Hodshi. They came
        to Dan Jaan and around to Sidon '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and came to the fortress of Tyre and all the cities of the Hivites
        and the Canaanites. Then they went out to the Negev of Judah at Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They went about through all the land, and they came to Jerusalem
        at the end of nine months and twenty days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Joab gave the number of the counting of the people to the king.
        Israel was eight hundred thousand valiant warriors wielding the sword, and
        the men of Judah were five hundred thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The heart of David struck him after he had counted the people, and
        David said to Yahweh, \u201CI have sinned greatly in what I have done! So
        then, O Yahweh, please forgive the guilt of your servant because I have acted
        very foolishly.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When David got up in the morning, the word of Yahweh came to Gad
        the prophet, the seer of David, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CGo and speak to David, \u2018Thus says Yahweh, three things
        I am laying on you; choose for yourself one of them and I will do it to you.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Gad came to David, and he told him and said to him, \u201CShall
        seven years of famine in the land come to you? Or three months of your fleeing
        from your enemies while he is pursuing you? Or should there be three days
        of pestilence in your land? Now consider and decide what I must return to
        the one who sent me a word.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then David said to Gad, \u201CI am greatly distressed. Please let
        us fall into the hand of Yahweh, because he is great in his compassion; but
        into the hand of man don\u2019t let me fall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Yahweh sent a plague into Israel from the morning until the
        agreed time, and from the people from Dan to Beersheba, seventy thousand
        men died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the angel stretched out his hand to destroy Jerusalem, Yahweh
        regretted about the evil, and he said to the angel who brought destruction
        among the people, \u201CEnough, now relax your hand.\u201D Now the angel
        of Yahweh was at the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "David spoke to Yahweh when he saw the angel destroying among the
        people, and he said, \u201CLook, I have sinned and I have done wrong, but
        these sheep, what did they do? Please let your hand be against me and against
        the house of my father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Gad came to David on that same day and said to him, \u201CGo
        up and erect an altar to Yahweh at the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So David went up according to the word of Gad, as Yahweh had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Araunah looked down and saw the king and his servants coming over
        to him, so Araunah went out and bowed down before the king with his face
        to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Araunah said, \u201CWhy has my lord the king come to his servant?\u201D
        David said, \u201CTo buy from you the threshing floor, to build an altar
        to Yahweh who brought a halt to the plague on the people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Araunah said to David, \u201CLet my lord the king take and offer
        what is good in his eyes. Look, here are the cattle for the burnt offering
        and the threshing sledge and the yokes of the oxen for the firewood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "All of this Araunah hereby gives to the king.\u201D Then Araunah
        said to the king, \u201CMay Yahweh your God respond favorably for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the king said to Araunah, \u201CNo, but I will certainly buy
        it from you for a price; I don\u2019t want to offer to Yahweh my God burnt
        offerings that cost me nothing.\u201D So David bought the threshing floor
        and the cattle for fifty shekels of silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'David built an altar to Yahweh there, and he offered burnt offerings
        and fellowship offerings. Then Yahweh responded to his prayer for the land
        and brought the plague to a halt from upon Israel. '
      comments: []
